&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4169&quot; title=&quot;PDFPrintable has subsampling but it can not be used&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4169&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4169&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: allow to set subsampling, as suggested by Marek Pribula&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16417694" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 28 Mar 2018 16:30:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1827930 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1827930&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1827930&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4169&quot; title=&quot;PDFPrintable has subsampling but it can not be used&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4169&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4169&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: allow to set subsampling, as suggested by Marek Pribula&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16417699" author="tilman" created="Wed, 28 Mar 2018 16:33:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done. I&apos;m surprised that subsampling has such a benefit in your printing, the only explanation would be that you have PDFs with images with a dpi higher than the one of your printer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16417932" author="marekpribula" created="Wed, 28 Mar 2018 19:02:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, that was exactly my case. I was working with extreme files since in our production we have no control over the supplied file and we need to process everything&#160;(with Xmx1g and sometimes only Xmx640m). So my file had the resolution much higher than my printers (again same as printers in production). Thanks for the update, looking forward to using it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
